news.title: Smartworks Coworking Spaces shares jump over 9% in market debut trade
news.para: Smartworks Coworking Spaces Ltd shares closed with a 9% premium, ending at Rs 445.10 on the BSE and Rs 445.05 on the NSE. The IPO, priced at Rs 407, saw strong investor interest, being oversubscribed 13.45 times. The company intends to utilize the raised capital of Rs 583 crore for business expansion and debt reduction.

news.title: How climate-resilient infrastructure can shape India’s future
news.para: India is undergoing a major infrastructure transformation. The National Infrastructure Pipeline aims to invest in key sectors. Urban population is rapidly growing, especially in Tier II and III cities. Climate change poses significant challenges. Integrating climate resilience into infrastructure is essential. This includes using green infrastructure and renewable systems. It also involves leveraging technology and climate risk mapping.

news.title: Rajasthan's new building bylaws: Impact, challenges and opportunities
news.para: Rajasthan has implemented new building bylaws. These bylaws aim to structure urban growth in cities like Jaipur and Udaipur. The rules reduce setbacks for smaller plots. They also revise group housing norms and township planning. The goal is to encourage sustainable building practices. These changes could lead to more planned and people-friendly cities. Approvals are likely to be quicker.

news.title: Rent pacts with developers of buildings under redevelopment to be accepted for passport: Minister
news.para: Maharashtra government will address passport verification problems. These problems are faced by citizens in buildings undergoing redevelopment. Minister Yogesh Kadam assured the assembly of this action. Current address verification is crucial for national security. The government will consider temporary addresses with rent agreements. They will also launch an awareness campaign. This campaign will inform citizens about the verification process.

news.title: Kalpataru's profit down 42% to ₹14 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Kalpataru Ltd experienced a 42% drop in net profit, reaching Rs 14.05 crore in Q4 FY25, compared to Rs 24.30 crore in the previous year. Despite this, total income increased to Rs 667.21 crore. For the entire fiscal year, the company reported a net profit of Rs 21.62 crore, a significant improvement from the previous year's loss.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body commissions construction and demolition waste plant
news.para: Ludhiana's Municipal Corporation has launched a construction and demolition waste processing plant after years of delays. Funded by the Swachh Bharat and Smart City Missions, the ₹7.39 crore facility aims to process 100 tonnes of debris daily, converting it into reusable materials like tiles and bricks.

news.title: NHB goes public with refinance list to curb misuse
news.para: To enhance transparency and prevent misuse, the National Housing Bank (NHB) has disclosed its refinance beneficiaries after fraud allegations against Aviom India Housing Finance. NHB aims to stop entities from misusing its name to secure loans. The regulator has also reformed its disbursal process for equitable fund distribution across the housing finance sector.

news.title: Rajasthan government to carry out feasibility studies for satellite towns around Jaipur
news.para: Rajasthan is planning satellite towns near Jaipur, inspired by GIFT City and HITEC City, focusing on hi-tech development. Locations like Bassi, Bagru, Chomu, and Kotputli are being considered. The government is conducting feasibility studies, including metro connectivity within a 20-40 km radius.

news.title: Ghaziabad: UPSIDA allots over 200 industrial plots lying idle for years
news.para: To address land scarcity hindering industrial growth in Ghaziabad, UPSIDA has subdivided and allotted 211 underutilized plots in Sahibabad Industrial Area. A revised policy allows owners of struggling industries to sell off 75% of their land in smaller parcels, fostering new industrial clusters.

news.title: Auda’s past plans erode Ahmedabad’s urban lakes
news.para: Past Town Planning schemes by AUDA in Ahmedabad have significantly reduced the land area of several lakes and ponds, despite state policy prohibiting such reductions. Areas like Thaltej, Bopal, and Vastrapur have witnessed shrinking water body areas after integration into AMC limits.

news.title: City to grow taller under Chennai development body's third master plan
news.para: Chennai is set for a major urban transformation. CMDA is developing a new master plan. It focuses on vertical growth with higher FSI in specific zones. The plan includes mixed-use developments and infrastructure upgrades. Focus is on integrating slum communities and flexible land use. K P Subramanian emphasizes cautious FSI increases.

news.title: Delhi: MCD writes to cops for assistance in evacuation of Signature View Apartments
news.para: MCD has requested Delhi Police's assistance in evacuating 336 flats at Signature View Apartments, deemed unsafe by IIT Delhi and the Delhi High Court. The court ordered demolition and rebuilding after MCD declared the complex uninhabitable in 2023. While DDA set a July 31 evacuation deadline, residents claim insufficient notice and seek clarity on rent compensation before vacating.

news.title: Over 26,000 flats in stalled Amrapali projects ready, 8,000 by September 2025
news.para: NBCC will now complete 8,000 Amrapali flats by September 2025, delayed from March due to GRAP restrictions and funding issues. Of the 37,000 units, 26,800 are constructed, with 13,300 buyers receiving possession. Adarsh Awas Yojna, with 2,000 flats, will be ready by March 2026, marking the final stage of the project.

news.title: Embassy REIT to tap debt market with ₹20 billion bond sale: Sources
news.para: Embassy Office Parks REIT plans to raise 20 billion rupees. The fund raising will be through five-year corporate bonds. Discussions with bankers are underway. The real estate investment trust aims to finalize the funding this month. The bonds have a 'AAA' rating from Crisil. This sale could attract mutual funds and insurance firms.

news.title: Starwood Property to buy Fundamental Income Properties for about $2.2 billion
news.para: Starwood Property Trust is set to acquire Fundamental Income Properties, a real estate operating platform, for approximately $2.2 billion. The acquisition, encompassing 467 properties across 44 states, will be financed through a combination of cash, debt, and equity, including the assumption of Fundamental's $1.3 billion in existing financing.

news.title: National Association of Realtors defeats Utah brokerage's antitrust lawsuit
news.para: A US court dismissed Homie Technology's lawsuit against the National Association of Realtors. Homie accused the realtor group of antitrust violations. The judge stated Homie did not provide enough evidence of harm. The judge also said the claims were untimely. The realtor association welcomed the ruling. They denied their policies hurt Homie. The association had previously settled a commission-related lawsuit.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 50 acres land in Raipur
news.para: Godrej Properties has expanded its footprint by acquiring 50 acres in Raipur for plotted residential development, projecting a saleable area of 9.5 lakh sq ft. MD & CEO Gaurav Pandey stated this move aligns with their strategy to strengthen presence in emerging markets.

news.title: Salman Khan sells his apartment for ₹5.35 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Salman Khan finalized the sale of his 1,318 sq ft apartment in Shiv Asthan Heights, Bandra West, Mumbai, for ₹5.35 crore, which includes three car parking spaces. The transaction, registered in July 2025, involved a stamp duty payment of ₹32.01 lakh and registration charges of ₹30,000.

news.title: Indian mining and construction equipment industry to report 2-5% volume growth in FY26: ICRA
news.para: The Indian mining and construction equipment (MCE) industry anticipates muted growth of 2-5% in FY26, reaching 1.43-1.47 lakh units, according to ICRA. While exports showed strong growth, domestic demand was hampered by tepid award activity and CEV-V norm implementation, leading to higher costs and squeezed OEM margins. Recovery hinges on improved traction in H2 FY26.

news.title: Two-day consultations on Visakhapatnam development body's master plan
news.para: VMRDA Chairman Pranav Gopal and Metropolitan Commissioner KS Viswanathan will personally address public concerns regarding the master plan on July 16 and 17. This concludes a month of consultations across Anakapalli, Visakhapatnam, and Vizianagaram districts.
